{"ticker": "CMPS", "company": "COMPASS PATHWAYS PLC", "weight_sum": 2.36, "etfs": ["ARKG"], "is_private": false, "query": "($CMPS OR \"Compass Pathways\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since:2026-04-29 until:2026-05-01", "n_fetched": 1, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2049498419035816421", "url": "https://x.com/filipsamardzicc/status/2049498419035816421", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/filipsamardzicc/status/2049498419035816421", "text": "$DFTX $ATAI $CMPS\n\n\u201cPsychedelics are having a flashback. This one comes with investors. And though researchers have been intrigued by the therapeutic potential of psychedelic medicine for decades, this time the mood feels different: restrictions are loosening, investors are circling and the wellness world is ready to pounce.\n\nPsychedelics are now being recast as the next breakthrough in behavioral healthcare.\n\n\u201cPatients are seeking remedies with effects that are simultaneously rapid, durable and effective,\u201d says David Marcovitz, M.D., Associate Professor of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences at Vanderbilt Health and co-founder of Valence, an integrated program for business leaders and their families. \u201cWe are seeing that the demand for such medicines can lead the market to try to cater to those desires.\n\nThe demand is real. Millions remain underserved by traditional mental health systems.\u201d\n\nhttps://t.co/8Lub3nOMjX", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 4, "replyCount": 0, "likeCount": 21, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 1158, "createdAt": "Wed Apr 29 14:37:55 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 3, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049498419035816421", "displayTextRange": [0, 274], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "filipsamardzicc", "url": "https://x.com/filipsamardzicc", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/filipsamardzicc", "id": "1975668017469267972", "name": "filip", "i